      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@achow101: I believe that it could not dip below 1 available input, since there were always two created and (n-1) added to the available_coins. Now, it should be impossible for the count to dip below the initial count because it consumes a maximum of two inputs and also adds at least two coins to available_coins every iteration.\r\n\r\nHappy to add an assert, though",
